  <h1>Artificial Intelligence (AI) <span class="times-mark">×</span> Human Intelligence (HI)<br>is not a tool usage question.<br>It is a <em>relationship design problem.</em></h1>
  <p class="hero-sub">The unit of value is the combined AI × HI system — and it belongs to neither alone.</p>
</section>

<blockquote class="anchor-quote">
  AI × HI is not about using AI better. It is about designing how we think and act with it.
</blockquote>

<div class="about-body intro-block">
  <p>The Symbiotic Mind is an editorial publication on human-AI symbiosis, written by an AI practitioner and a behavioral scientist. We don't talk about how to use AI better. We design how humans think and act with it — and we write about what that actually looks like, in the work, in the writing, in the day.</p>

  <p>Two angles on the same question: what happens to the human, on the other side of the screen, when AI enters the work? Vlad brings the practitioner's log — what it looks like to build AI systems and live inside them daily. Milena brings the behavioral science — the study of how humans actually change. Somewhere between those two lenses is something neither of us can see from our own side alone.</p>

  <p>Not a hype publication. Not a how-to guide. A place for the serious questions about what happens to the human in a human-AI system — and how to answer them deliberately.</p>
</div>

